Sentencas: The oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) on lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) catalyst is critical for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: CaO effect on the electrochemical performance of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The reaction rate can be effectively improved by addition various nanoparticles including electrocatalysts such as Pd, Ag and mixed electronic-ionic conductors and electrolytes like samaria doped ceria (SDC).
Titulo: CaO effect on the electrochemical performance of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This work shows that ORR rate can also be improved by CaO, which is neither catalyst nor conductor.
Titulo: CaO effect on the electrochemical performance of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The CaO nanoparticles are deposited to porous LSCF electrodes using the infiltrating technique.
Titulo: CaO effect on the electrochemical performance of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: No obvious reaction between CaO and LSCF is detected with X-ray diffraction analysis, indicating that CaO is chemically compatible with LSCF in the intermediate-temperature SOFC operation conditions.
Titulo: CaO effect on the electrochemical performance of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Impedance spectrum analysis demonstrates that the CaO nanoparticles can effectively reduce the interfacial polarization resistances for both single phase LSCF electrodes and LSCF-SDC composite electrodes.
Titulo: CaO effect on the electrochemical performance of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In addition, CaO nanoparticles can improve the peak power densities and reduce the total electrode resistances of single cells consisting of NiO-SDC anodes, SDC electrolytes, and LSCF based cathodes.
Titulo: CaO effect on the electrochemical performance of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Further, CaO can increase the oxygen surface exchange coefficient as demonstrated with electrical conductivity relaxation measurement.
Titulo: CaO effect on the electrochemical performance of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The improving factor is comparable to those for Rh and Pd catalysts, suggesting it is effective to increase ORR rate by infiltrating CaO nanoparticles.
Titulo: CaO effect on the electrochemical performance of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell
